                <div class ="terms widget">
        <ul>
                        <li class="vothG_ghetto">
                <a name="vothG_ghetto"></a>
                <p>
                    <b>
                        <a href="#close" class="hide">
                            [x] click to close
                        </a>
                    </b>
                </p>
                <span class="term">
                    ghetto.
                </span>
                <span class="definition">
                    A Yiddish word referring to a walled section of a city in which Jews were required to live during the Middle Ages. The concept was revived by the Nazi regime as part of the "Final Solution" to the "Jewish Question." 
                </span>
            </li>
                        <li class="vothG_action">
                <a name="vothG_action"></a>
                <p>
                    <b>
                        <a href="#close" class="hide">
                            [x] click to close
                        </a>
                    </b>
                </p>
                <span class="term">
                    action.
                </span>
                <span class="definition">
                    Episodes of coordinated violence against Jewish communities, including the rounding up of Jews for deportation to ghettos, concentration camps, or killing centers.
                </span>
            </li>
                        <li class="vothG_commandant">
                <a name="vothG_commandant"></a>
                <p>
                    <b>
                        <a href="#close" class="hide">
                            [x] click to close
                        </a>
                    </b>
                </p>
                <span class="term">
                    commandant.
                </span>
                <span class="definition">
                    A commander of a Nazi camp. In the death camps the commandant was required to witness every gassing carried out through a peephole, and supervise both the preparations and the aftermath.
                </span>
            </li>
                    </ul>
    </div>
    <ul class="note_popup widget">
            </ul>
</div>
